        "subject": "LU-17000 lst: Fix unsed variable reported by valgrind",
        "message": "LU-17000 lst: Fix unsed variable reported by valgrind\n\nFix use of unsed variable reported by valgrind when\nusing command 'lst list_batch'\n\n$ valgrind lst list_batch\n==114042== Memcheck, a memory error detector\n==114042== Copyright (C) 2002-2022, and GNU GPL'd, by Julian Seward et al.\n==114042== Using Valgrind-3.22.0 and LibVEX; rerun with -h for copyright info\n==114042== Command: lst list_batch\n==114042==\n==114042== Conditional jump or move depends on uninitialised value(s)\n==114042==    at 0x484D759: strlen (vg_replace_strmem.c:502)\n==114042==    by 0x4A486B7: __vfprintf_internal (in /usr/lib64/libc.so.6)\n==114042==    by 0x4A33889: fprintf (in /usr/lib64/libc.so.6)\n==114042==    by 0x4083AC: lst_list_batch_all (lst.c:3098)\n==114042==    by 0x4083AC: jt_lst_list_batch (lst.c:3222)\n==114042==    by 0x4882964: cfs_parser_execarg (parser.c:177)\n==114042==    by 0x4882964: cfs_parser (parser.c:160)\n==114042==    by 0x4A0358F: (below main) (in /usr/lib64/libc.so.6)\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-lnet\nSigned-off-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nChange-Id: I5decf45ac2d759ad98e5cc301adfc06bbc3d0436\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60604\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Shaun Tancheff <shaun.tancheff@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
